OOC: If SS couldn't get him off the ground he probably
wouldn't be stupid enough to mention it, because he'd
prefer Tyreal not knowing about his ambitions.

BIC:  SS let go and rolled over beside Warhead dodging
most of the explosives (which probably landed back on
Warhead), but it still chared his transmetal plating
some.

SS:  YOU INSOLENT PIECE OF SCRAPE!

He transformed and fired 8 lasers from point-blank
range.

--- warriorazure <wingedwarrior41@...> wrote:
> OOC: Warhead is in vehicle mode, and he's too big to
> be lifted. At 
> most, SS could get on him.
> 
> Perceptor's shots missed both Burrock and Tyrael,
> but blew a few 
> nearby trees to splints. The stinger fired by
> Waspinator, however, was 
> straight on target. Burrock was thrown back a dozen
> meters, making him 
> lose his grip over Inferno. He splashed in the
> water, but before 
> anyone could track him up, he burrowed in the muddy
> pond's bottom.
> 
> Warhead tried to aim at Shadow Star. He fired many
> small explosives, 
> doing not much damage individually, but devastating
> in group.
> 
> Warhead: Cowardly foe! Do you think that you could
> be superior to 
> Milord Megatron? Diplomacy will not prevent your
> death at my gun!
> 
> At the mention of ruling the universe made by his
> lieutenant, Tyrael 
> frowned. He was going to have a long strategic chat,
> but that would 
> wait. Megatron was out now, and the true fight would
> start.
> 
> Tyrael: I see you have come Megatron. Now come. You
> will learn why 
> they call me the Blue Firestorm!
> 
> He showered his enemy with a rain of light bolts, no
> bigger than 
> needles.
> 
>
